00:50:06.601 --> 00:50:09.590
So I think it really
is about being

00:50:09.590 --> 00:50:12.140
intentional about the
gathering, about the group,

00:50:12.140 --> 00:50:14.420
about the community
that you create

00:50:14.420 --> 00:50:16.790
when under this banner of
Asian American, you know.

00:50:19.860 --> 00:50:22.500
VALARIE KAUR: Sonia
is coming to my mind.

00:50:22.500 --> 00:50:26.010
Sonia is a pharmacist
in Chicago,

00:50:26.010 --> 00:50:27.420
an Indian American mother.

00:50:27.420 --> 00:50:29.680
And I was with her last week.

00:50:29.680 --> 00:50:32.400
And she came to me after
work completely distressed

00:50:32.400 --> 00:50:36.990
saying that she was at the cash
register when a man walked,

00:50:36.990 --> 00:50:38.610
a customer walked,
into the store

00:50:38.610 --> 00:50:41.280
and started to say
all of my problems

00:50:41.280 --> 00:50:44.370
are because of you foreigners
and ranted on and on,

00:50:44.370 --> 00:50:45.990
basically echoing
what he has heard

00:50:45.990 --> 00:50:47.620
from the President
and people in power

00:50:47.620 --> 00:50:49.020
but directing it at Sonia.

00:50:49.020 --> 00:50:51.420
And she stays quiet
working the register.

00:50:51.420 --> 00:50:54.060
Her white coworkers
are next to her.

00:50:54.060 --> 00:50:55.160
The man leaves.

00:50:55.160 --> 00:50:58.440
And after the man leaves the
white coworkers turn to her

00:50:58.440 --> 00:50:59.910
and say are you OK?

00:50:59.910 --> 00:51:00.720
She's shaken.

00:51:00.720 --> 00:51:03.070
She says yes, I'm OK.

00:51:03.070 --> 00:51:04.980
And she says to me,
what should I have done?

00:51:04.980 --> 00:51:05.970
I feel so ashamed.

00:51:05.970 --> 00:51:06.970
I should have done more.

00:51:06.970 --> 00:51:10.500
And I said no, actually
it's not on you to do more.

00:51:10.500 --> 00:51:12.450
It was on your
coworkers in that moment

00:51:12.450 --> 00:51:14.010
in their relative
positions of power

00:51:14.010 --> 00:51:16.410
to stand up and
defend you, to create

00:51:16.410 --> 00:51:19.860
the culture in the workplace
that they want to create.

00:51:19.860 --> 00:51:22.080
And I told her the story
has been keeping me alive.

00:51:22.080 --> 00:51:25.980
The story of a Punjabi language
professor here in San Jose.

00:51:25.980 --> 00:51:28.590
After 9/11, all
those years ago, he

00:51:28.590 --> 00:51:32.220
was sitting on a bus in
San Jose on his way home

00:51:32.220 --> 00:51:34.080
from the university.

00:51:34.080 --> 00:51:35.850
He was looking out
the window when

00:51:35.850 --> 00:51:38.610
a man at the front of the bus
stood up, turned around, red

00:51:38.610 --> 00:51:41.910
in the face, and began
pointing at him and saying,

00:51:41.910 --> 00:51:44.310
hey, you f-ing terrorists,
go back to your country.

00:51:44.310 --> 00:51:45.090
Get off this bus.

00:51:45.090 --> 00:51:46.950
Go back to where you come from.

00:51:46.950 --> 00:51:49.020
And my professor wears
a turban and beard,

00:51:49.020 --> 00:51:51.939
looks like my grandfather,
looks out the windows

00:51:51.939 --> 00:51:53.730
and is just praying
for the moment to pass.

00:51:53.730 --> 00:51:54.230
Right?

00:51:54.230 --> 00:51:59.170
What else can he do but
pray for the moment to pass.

00:51:59.170 --> 00:52:02.130
Something remarkable happens.

00:52:02.130 --> 00:52:05.940
The other people on the
bus began to stand up--

00:52:05.940 --> 00:52:09.330
white, black, Latino,
Asian, they stand up.

00:52:09.330 --> 00:52:10.740
And they take this man's arm.

00:52:10.740 --> 00:52:13.560
And they say sit down, sit down.

00:52:13.560 --> 00:52:16.000
And the man sits down.

00:52:16.000 --> 00:52:20.170
The bus comes to a stop and my
professor gets off this bus.

00:52:20.170 --> 00:52:21.779
And the man gets off this bus.

00:52:21.779 --> 00:52:23.320
And the man walks
up to my professor,

00:52:23.320 --> 00:52:24.194
and puts out his arm.

00:52:24.194 --> 00:52:30.340
And at this point, I'm waiting
for the violence to happen.

00:52:30.340 --> 00:52:36.690
But the man takes my professor's
hand and shakes it, and says,

00:52:36.690 --> 00:52:41.160
I just lost my granddaughter
in that second plane that

00:52:41.160 --> 00:52:43.510
went into that second tower.

00:52:43.510 --> 00:52:45.560
I am angry.

00:52:45.560 --> 00:52:46.090
I am sorry.

00:52:49.740 --> 00:52:53.280
What stays with
me from that story

00:52:53.280 --> 00:52:58.670
is that we are the
people on that bus.

00:52:58.670 --> 00:53:02.270
We are the people who in the
most ordinary circumstances,

00:53:02.270 --> 00:53:07.640
in a Google roundtable, in a
conference room here on campus,

00:53:07.640 --> 00:53:11.450
on a bus ride home, in the
streets, in the school yards,

00:53:11.450 --> 00:53:15.110
at our kitchen tables, we
can stand up and do the most

00:53:15.110 --> 00:53:17.990
courageous things to
defend and protect

00:53:17.990 --> 00:53:21.260
people who are in harm's way,
to create the kind of workplace

00:53:21.260 --> 00:53:23.750
culture, but also the
culture in our country

00:53:23.750 --> 00:53:26.430
that we are longing for.

00:53:26.430 --> 00:53:28.690
Each of you has
that warrior in you.

00:53:28.690 --> 00:53:33.000
Each of you has the ability
to stand, to stand up.

00:53:33.000 --> 00:53:35.600
And we will only do this
if we do it together.

00:53:35.600 --> 00:53:36.740
Because here's the truth.

00:53:36.740 --> 00:53:39.367
This is a dark moment
in our country.

00:53:39.367 --> 00:53:40.700
I've been fighting for 15 years.

00:53:40.700 --> 00:53:44.220
I don't know how I'm going to
this explain this to my son.

00:53:44.220 --> 00:53:45.240
I'm touring preschools.

00:53:45.240 --> 00:53:47.220
And I can't even send him to
preschool right now because I

00:53:47.220 --> 00:53:48.970
know the data on
bullying for a little boy

00:53:48.970 --> 00:53:51.540
with long hair who keeps his
hair as part of his faith.

00:53:51.540 --> 00:53:53.322
This a dark moment
for me personally.

00:53:53.322 --> 00:53:54.780
It's a dark moment
for our country.

00:53:54.780 --> 00:53:58.526
And so if this is dark for you,
know that you are not alone.

00:53:58.526 --> 00:54:00.900
And this is the one thing I
leave with you, the one thing

00:54:00.900 --> 00:54:05.310
that I have held onto
as a mother is this.

00:54:05.310 --> 00:54:08.970
What if-- what if
this darkness is not

00:54:08.970 --> 00:54:11.540
the darkness of the tomb?

00:54:11.540 --> 00:54:16.110
What if this darkness is
the darkness of the womb?

00:54:16.110 --> 00:54:19.740
What if our America is
not dead, but a country

00:54:19.740 --> 00:54:21.740
still waiting to be born?

00:54:21.740 --> 00:54:22.240
Right?

00:54:22.240 --> 00:54:25.320
Langston Hughes says let America
be America again, the land that

00:54:25.320 --> 00:54:26.235
has never been.

00:54:26.235 --> 00:54:27.829
It has never been that for me.

00:54:27.829 --> 00:54:30.120
It has never been that for
black folks in this country,

00:54:30.120 --> 00:54:31.350
for indigenous folks.

00:54:31.350 --> 00:54:34.510
The land that has never
been and yet still must be.

00:54:34.510 --> 00:54:37.870
So I swear this oath let
America be America again.

00:54:37.870 --> 00:54:40.320
Let us make it so.

00:54:40.320 --> 00:54:44.100
Because what if this moment is
our nation's great transition?

00:54:44.100 --> 00:54:47.040
What does the
midwife ask us to do?

00:54:47.040 --> 00:54:51.520
She says to breathe.

00:54:51.520 --> 00:54:53.560
And she says to push.

00:54:53.560 --> 00:54:55.780
Because if we don't
push, we will die.

00:54:55.780 --> 00:55:00.130
Like if we don't push, our
nation, our America will die.

00:55:00.130 --> 00:55:02.680
We don't go into battle
alone, there's warriors,

00:55:02.680 --> 00:55:04.510
and we don't give birth alone.

00:55:04.510 --> 00:55:06.820
So I say hold fast
to one another.

00:55:06.820 --> 00:55:10.090
Hold fast to your coworkers,
your family, your friends.

00:55:10.090 --> 00:55:12.579
Hold fast to one another
as brothers and sisters

00:55:12.579 --> 00:55:13.120
in the fight.

00:55:13.120 --> 00:55:15.400
Help one another stand
up when you need to.

00:55:15.400 --> 00:55:17.920
Help one another
breathe and push.

00:55:17.920 --> 00:55:19.774
And then breathe and then push.

00:55:19.774 --> 00:55:21.690
And then keep breathing
and then keep pushing.

